 East London - Police in East London are investigating a fatal shooting incident in which two people lost their lives. "It is alleged that approximately 19:30 on Thursday, a man and a woman, between the ages of 49 and 52 years old, were found lying in a pool of blood outside a house at Jade Street, in Amalinda, East London," said police spokesperson, Captain Hazel Mqala. "It is further alledged that while the woman was inside her car talking on the phone, her ex-boyfriend entered the house carrying a firearm on one hand and a knife on the other hand." Capt Mqala said that the ex-boyfriend allegedly then asked a tenant about the whereabouts of the woman, but he was informed that she was not in the house. "The suspect then walked outside and saw the victim getting out of her vehicle," she added. "It is alledged that he then shot the victim on the upper body and then shot himself also in the upper body." Capt Mqala said that East London police and paramedics were called to the scene. However, the man and the woman were declared dead. "A 9mm Norinco pistol with a serial number was found on the scene." She said that a case of murder and an inquest docket has been opened for investigation by East London police. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 